    • Method Detail

      • setBatchProperties

        void setBatchProperties(Optional<Integer> max_objects,
                        Optional<Long> size_kb,
                        Optional<Duration> flush_interval,
                        Optional<Integer> write_threads)
        Sets the batching parameters
        Parameters:
        max_objects - - the max number of records before a batch is flushed
        size_kb - - the max size before a batch is flushed
        flush_interval - - the max time before a batch is flushed
        write_threads - - the requested number of write threads (this is not guaranteed to be granted, but will be taken into account)

      • storeObjects

        void storeObjects(List<O> new_objects,
                  boolean replace_if_present)
        Efficiently store the list of objects with the subservice's batching parameters
        Parameters:
        new_objects - - the list of objects to store
        replace_if_present - - if true, will overwrite existing elements; if false may error in which case the behavior of other objects is undefined (but this is safe to use if using UUIDs for _id or ommitting _id, which is equivalent). Some technologies may not support replacing, in which case it is ignored.
